properties.sfomuseum:description: Rehoused scrapbook of Panagra President Harold Roig; photographs and letters regarding his visit to South America. Includes:a. letter: to Mr. de Groot from Walton Jones re: photographs Foreign Minister Guarderas presenting Roig with the National Medal "Al Merito", dated June 23, 1943b. letter: to Roig from Walton Jones regarding enclosed photographs, a copy of the Foreign Minister's speech, and newspaper clippings, dated June 24, 1943c. photograph: Roig and others at the hotel Grace y Cia in La Paz Boliviad. photograph: Roig and others in front of a Panagra planee. photograph: Roig arrives at La Paz Airport, dated July 2, 1943f. photograph: banquetg. photograph: formal photograph of Roig and dignitariesh. photograph: Roig's press conference at the Carrera Hoteli. photograph: Roig and others in front of a Panagra plane in Argentinaj. photograph: Josh Lee, Chairman of the Civil Aeronautics Board at the press conference in the Hotel Carrerak. photograph: American Ambassador Bowers, Roig, and Lee at Los Cerrillos Airportl. photograph: Roig and other dignitaries stand in front of a Panagra planem. photograph: Roig posing at a desk in Santiagon. photograph: luncheon at the "Club National" of Lima, Peru, dated July 24, 1943o. photograph: luncheon at the "Club National" of Lima, Peru, dated July 24, 1943p. photograph: luncheon at the "Club National" of Lima, Peru, dated July 24, 1943q. photograph: luncheon at the "Club National" of Lima, Peru, dated July 24, 1943
properties.wof:name: scrapbook: Panagra (Pan American-Grace Airways), South America
